The paper focuses on the interaction between humans and robots, specifically in the context of trust and cognitive load. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Human-Robot Interaction (cs.HRI), and Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). However, given the emphasis on human-robot interaction and trust, as well as the use of robots in the study, cs.HRI and cs.RO are the most likely categories. The paper also involves cognitive load, which is a key aspect of human-robot interaction, and thus cs.HC is also a likely category. Finally, the paper touches on the impact of robot error rates, which could be relevant to cybersecurity, hence cs.CYBER is also a possible category.
